            . I am clerk to Mr. Henry Buckley, an <rs id="t18331017-26-viclabel143" type="occupation">oil-cloth manufacturer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-26-victim355 t18331017-26-viclabel143"></join>, who lives in the <placeName id="t18331017-26-crimeloc144">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-26-crimeloc144" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331017-26-crimeloc144" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-26-off141 t18331017-26-crimeloc144"></join>; on the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183310170024"></xptr>14th of September, I saw the prisoner going out of his shop with this oil-cloth on his shoulder, I ran after him and took him in the street, with it on his shoulder - I brought him back with it - I knew the pattern and the quality of it - when I brought the prisoner back he sat down for some time and then ran out - he was brought back by 
               <persName id="t18331017-26-person357">
                  Robert 
                  Carr
               <interp inst="t18331017-26-person357" type="surname" value="Carr"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-26-person357" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-26-person357" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - I had seen the oil-cloth safe an hour before.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CHURCHILL. Q. Has your master any partner? A. No - the prisoner made no resistance.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331017-26-person358">
                  ROBERT 
                  CARR
               <interp inst="t18331017-26-person358" type="surname" value="CARR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-26-person358" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-26-person358" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was a police-officer: on the day stated I was in my shop, I heard a cry of "Stop thief;" I went out and saw the prisoner running - I went and took him; when I got him to the end of Drury-court, a man directed me to the prosecutor's shop - I received this oil-cloth.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did he appear sober? A. Yes, perfectly.</p>
